high school students it's the idea of a vector&nbsp;
what exactly is a vector well there are a number&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:34.140 --> 00:00:42.660
of possible answers we could say that the vector&nbsp;
is a directed line segment and that captures very&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:51.420
nicely what it is that we have in mind we have in&nbsp;
mind a quantity which has both a direction and a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:00:51.420 --> 00:01:00.870
magnitude so here's a vector called V or a picture&nbsp;
of one and because it's a directed line segment we&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:00.870 --> 00:01:07.560
do not mind if we translate it we still call that&nbsp;
the same vector so these two vectors over here&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:13.650
which are parallel to this one and have the same&nbsp;
length we consider them to be the same vectors&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:13.650 --> 00:01:19.500
this will example here that's a vector which is&nbsp;
a different direction and has a different length&nbsp;&nbsp;

